## 3. Color‑gradient shader on the strands

For a smooth gradient along the Y‑axis of each strand, use a custom ShaderMaterial.

```js
const strandShader = {
  uniforms: {
    colorA: { value: new THREE.Color(0x3194d0) },
    colorB: { value: new THREE.Color(0x3dbcb0) }
  },
  vertexShader: `
    varying float vYpos;
    void main() {
      vYpos = position.y;
      gl_Position = projectionMatrix * modelViewMatrix * vec4(position,1.0);
    }
  `,
  fragmentShader: `
    uniform vec3 colorA;
    uniform vec3 colorB;
    varying float vYpos;
    void main() {
      float t = (vYpos +  totalH/2.0) / totalH;   // remap y to [0,1]
      vec3 color = mix(colorA, colorB, t);
      gl_FragColor = vec4(color, 1.0);
    }
  `
};

const gradMat = new THREE.ShaderMaterial({
  ...strandShader,
  side: THREE.DoubleSide
});

// rebuild group geometry with the gradient material
group.clear();
group.add(new THREE.Mesh(
  new THREE.TubeGeometry(curve1, totalPts, tubeR, 8, false),
  gradMat
));
group.add(new THREE.Mesh(
  new THREE.TubeGeometry(curve2, totalPts, tubeR, 8, false),
